@database PopstringClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Popstring Class"


Popstring class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "GroupClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Popstring class is used to create a popstring, which is an object made
  of:
     o a string object - a generic object
     o a button object - a generic object
     o a window object - a window object

  Any time the button object is "pressed" the window is opened.

  See @{"Popobject" LINK "PopobjectFunctions.guide/Main"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Button@{fg text}
  S I
  It may be omitted: a popup button is used

  @{fg shine}ButtonCycleChain@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the auto button will be in the window cycle chain

  @{fg shine}CloseFun@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can supply a macro in this attribute: anytime
  the object is closed, CloseFun macro is executed with one
  argument: the success flag. The macro must be an
  ARexx-in-line-string-macro designed to be very fast.

  @{fg shine}Open@{fg text}
  B GN
  Set and notified when the window is opened/closed.

  @{fg shine}OpenFun@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can supply a macro in this attribute: anytime
  the object is to be opened, OpenFun macro is executed (with no
  argument). The object is opened if and only if the macro
  returns 1. The macro must be an ARexx-in-line-string-macro
  designed to be very fast.

  @{fg shine}String@{fg text}
  S I IND
  A String class object.

  @{fg shine}Success@{fg text}
  B GN
  Set and notified when the window is closed. The popobject
  doesn't know anything about it: you must tell him what success
  means via a notify, e.g.:
      call Notify("pw","CloseRequest",1,"ps","Close",0)
      call Notify("cs","Pressed",0,"ps","Close",1)

  @{fg shine}Toggle@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Window@{fg text}
  S I IND

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Close@{fg text}
  [success/N]
  success is an ARexx boolean. It is passed to CloseFun, if
  supplied.

  @{fg shine}Open@{fg text}
  -

@EndNode

